## <a id='v130'></a>v1.3.0

**Release Date:**  December 29, 2017

Features included in this release:

- Support for asynchronously replicating data across PCF foundations
- Support for `AsyncEventListeners` for **write-behind** to a data store e.g. a Database 
- Support for `Functions` to perform Map/Reduce style computation on the data
- Secured GemFire processes using BOSH Process Manager

Known issues in this release:

- If you're upgrading to PCC v1.3.0 and you created service keys on PCC before you installed v1.3.0,
  delete and recreate the service keys so that the users are assigned roles in the cluster.
  Then, rebind all your apps.

    For information about how to do these tasks, see
    [Delete a Service Key](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-0/devguide/services/service-keys.html),
    [Create Service Keys](developer.html#create-service-key), and
    [Bind an App to a Service Instance](developer.html#bind-service).

